body:
Safari seems to deal great with multiple cookie in one Set-Cookie header.
But Firefox seems to need one header per cookie.

In that file http://github.com/visionmedia/express/blob/master/lib/express/plugins/cookie.js
Could you consider this patch :
    response: function(event) {
        if (event.response.cookies.length)
            event.request.header('set-cookie', event.response.cookies.join("\nset-cookie: "))
    }

It's not the cleanest way, but headers are stored in an object, not an array

They can be made available by adding `true` as the first arg to `process.mixin` on line 74 of view.js:

```
if (layout)
    self.render('layout.' + type + '.' + ext, process.mixin(true, options, {
        layout: false,
        locals: {
            body: content
        }
    }))
```

